The paper focuses on improving the feedback generation process in recommender systems through changes in the user interface design. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of interface design on the quality and quantity of feedback data, which is relevant to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions information foraging theory, which is a concept related to Cybernetics (cs.CY) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
